Speaker, Kwara State House of Assembly, Rt Honourable Salihu Yakubu Danladi has congratulated Nigerians as the country marks its 59th independence anniversary. The Speaker, in a statement signed by his Special Assistant, Media, Ibrahim Sheriff, said that “while thanking God Almighty over the relative peace we have in Nigeria despite our diversities and challenges, we pray peace returns to troubled parts of the country.” ALSO READ:  Policeman allegedly kills female colleague in Delta Nigeria @ 59: Nigeria will be sitting on time bomb if…… #NigeriaAt59: President Buhari’s Independence Day speech… Kidnappers yet to release wife of railway boss as police… Nigeria@59: 9-year-old Ifeanyichukwu, nine others grab… The Gwanara born legislator, however, charged Nigerians to strengthen their patriotism and belief in the country, noting that the selflessness and sacrifices of our heroes past were borne out of their unequalled patriotism that earned us the independence we enjoy today. “It is therefore imperative for us all to recognize our roles as leaders, citizens and relevant stakeholders in realizing the vision of our heroes past; vision of a peaceful, united and prosperous Nigeria. “Let us continue to pray for Nigeria and do all in our ability to sustain the spirit of relentlessness, perseverance and sacrifice that led to our independence to realize a greater Nigeria that we can be more proud of,” he said. How premature ejaculation  and small penis almost ruin my marriage and made my wife cheat on me, until my Abuja doctor recommend this powerful but simple solution that work wonder...DONT BE A VICTIM.... SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE
